@nishantmonu51 : investigating against

```
GroupByQuery{limitSpec=NoopLimitSpec, dimFilter=null, granularity=AllGranularity, dimensions=[DefaultDimensionSpec{dimension='l_linenumber', outputName='l_linenumber'}, DefaultDimensionSpec{dimension='l_suppkey', outputName='l_suppkey'}, DefaultDimensionSpec{dimension='l_shipinstruct', outputName='l_shipinstruct'}], aggregatorSpecs=[DoubleSumAggregatorFactory{fieldName='l_tax_doublesum', name='L_TAX_'}, DoubleSumAggregatorFactory{fieldName='l_discount_doublesum', name='L_DISCOUNT_'}, DoubleSumAggregatorFactory{fieldName='l_extendedprice_doublesum', name='L_EXTENDEDPRICE_'}, LongSumAggregatorFactory{fieldName='l_quantity_longsum', name='L_QUANTITY_'}, CountAggregatorFactory{name='count'}
```

@mrijke to access the estimated cardinality as part of a post-aggregation instead of the raw hyperUnique sketch of the cardinality aggregator you have to use the [`hyperUniqueCardinality` post-aggregator](http://druid.io/docs/latest/Post-aggregations.html#hyperunique-cardinality-post-aggregator) to convert the sketch to a floating point estimate. For example:

``` json
"aggregations" : [
  {"type" : "count", "name" : "rows"},
  {"type" : "cardinality", "name" : "dim_card", "fieldName" : "mydimension"}
],
"postAggregations" : [{
  "type"   : "arithmetic",
  "name"   : "average_rows_per_unique_value",
  "fn"     : "/",
  "fields" : [
    { "type" : "fieldAccess", "name" : "rows", "fieldName" : "rows" },
    { "type" : "hyperUniqueCardinality", "fieldName" : "dim_card" }
  ]
}]
```
